## 9. What Cursor Must Not Do

This is a safety list. If Cursor finds itself doing any of the following, it should stop and re-read this PRD:

- DO NOT modify `lib/auth/server.ts`, `lib/auth/org-access.ts`, or `lib/auth/platform-admin.ts`
- DO NOT modify `app/(dashboard)/layout.tsx` or any other layout file
- DO NOT modify `lib/supabase/server.ts`, `lib/supabase/client.ts`, or `lib/supabase/admin.ts`
- DO NOT add any Supabase calls inside `middleware.ts` — middleware runs on the Edge runtime and the Supabase SSR client requires Node.js `cookies()` from `next/headers`
- DO NOT add any redirect logic to the middleware
- DO NOT modify `next.config.ts` unless there is a specific, documented reason
- DO NOT create any new components, pages, or server actions
- DO NOT run any database migrations
- DO NOT modify `vercel.json`
- DO NOT touch any file in `lib/verticals/` — that is Phase 2
- DO NOT touch any email templates in `lib/email/templates/`
- DO NOT add `middleware.ts` inside the `app/` directory — it must be at the repo root (sibling to `next.config.ts`)

